      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i'm working on this embedded c++ project and the heap is just climbing constantly. i'm using new/delete but i can't see where the leak is happening. here is the snippet from my main loop:\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data() {\n    int* data_buffer = new int[1024];\n    \n    if (read_sensor(data_buffer) != SUCCESS) {\n        // log error and return\n        return;\n    }\n\n    // process the data...\n    for (int i = 0; i < 1024; i++) {\n        data_buffer[i] *= 2;\n    }\n\n    // compute some stats\n    calculate_stats(data_buffer);\n\n    delete[] data_buffer;\n}\n```\n\nlooks fine to me? why would this cause a memory leak?",
